This paper deals with dynamic algorithms for maintaining approximate vertex covers and fractional matchings in graphs and hypergraphs. The problem involves updating the solution as edges are inserted or deleted from the graph/hypergraph. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS) and "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM). The problem of maintaining maximum matchings and minimum vertex covers is also related to "Graph Theory" (cs.GT) and "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC). Finally, the use of amortized analysis in the algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the category of "Numerical Analysis" (cs.NA).
